snippet.textDisplay: Will you take a stand against the drag culture being pushed on children? Have you seen the tik tok video of a drag queen dancing seductively for a 6 yo girls b-day party like a lap dance.  I am gay and have no issue with drag for adult entertainment.  But there is a new push to normalize exposing children to drag in age inappropriate ways.   Progressives argue this is some way to help kids who deal with gender confusion or issues coming to terms with their orientation.  I argue this behavior is turning the average person who doesn't mind gay people into all out hateful bigots. And I can hardly blame them.  Drag has no place in child entertainment.
